## GET Invitations

<%= partial "includes/APIReference/Invitations/Examples/get.tmpl.erb" %>

Finds the invitations for all of the users

### HTTP Request

<img src="images/get.png" alt="get"/><api>https://rest.tsheets.com/api/v1/invitations</api>

### Properties
_Pass the following paramaters to as the value to a 'data' property (see example)._

|                |             |             |
| -------------: | :---------: | ----------- |
| **modified_since_method**<br/>optional | _String_ | IOS 8061 Timestamp.  Will find all invitations modified since the included time. |
| **user_ids**<br/>optional | _String_ | Comma delimited list of user ids to inlcude. Will include all users by default |
| **supplemental_data**<br/>optional | _Boolean_ | Should we include supplmental data?  Default is yes. |
| **per_page**<br/>optional | _Int_ | How many results should we return per page?  Default is 50. |
| **page**<br/>optional | _Int_ | Should we include supplmental data?  Defaults is yes. |


### Status Codes

Each invitation that is created will come back with a `_status_code` and `_status_message` that will indicate whether the invitation was created successfully.  If there was a problem creating an invitation, there may also be an additional field, `_status_extra`, which will contain more details about the failure.

|         |          |
| :-----: | :------- |
| <code class="level200">201</code> | Ok. Request recieved and processed. |
| <code class="level400">400</code> | Bad Request. |

<aside class="notice">
The maximum batch size is <i>50</i> invitations. If exceeded, a <code class="standout">413: Request entity too large</code> HTTP response will be returned.
</aside>

